<h1>Commitment</h1>
<h2>Track your progress as you take the "Commit a Day" challenge</h2>

<div>
  <p>Commitment keeps you on track while working on side projects.</p>
  <p>Features include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Email notifications at a specific time each day reminding
      you to commit
    </li>
    <li>Interesting information about commit history</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div>
  <p>Check your progress</p>
  <%= form_for :user, url: user_path do |form| %>
    <%= form.label :username, 'Enter your github username' %>
    <%= form.text_field :username %>
    <%= form.submit %>
  <% end %>
</div>

<div>
  <p>Get started</p>
  <p>Step 1: Download and install the following git hook</p>
  <!-- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2293498/git-commit-hooks-global-settings -->
  <p>Step 2: Get committing!</p>
</div>

<div>
  <p>Can't think of a side project? Check out some of these:</p>
  <a href="https://projecteuler.net/">Project Euler</a>
</div>
